<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="61" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Asexual morph: mycelium consisting of septate, smooth hyphae, gradually becoming widen, thick-walled, darker and developing into meristematic chains of conidia. Conidia dark brown, thick-walled, smooth, rugose, globose with single central septa resulting from the differentiation of toruloid-like hyphal cells. Sexual morph: unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
